This doesn't work:
node.api('users').set_privilege('test')

This is because you can't run: username test no privilege. Instead you have to run username test no privilege 1 (the EOS default)

So this code:

```
cmd = 'username %s' % name
        if value is not None:
            if not isprivilege(value):
                raise TypeError('priviledge value must be between 0 and 15')
            cmd += ' privilege %s' % value
        else:
            cmd += ' no privilege'
        return self.configure(cmd)
```

Should change to:

```
cmd = 'username %s' % name
        if value is not None:
            if not isprivilege(value):
                raise TypeError('priviledge value must be between 0 and 15')
            cmd += ' privilege %s' % value
        else:
            cmd = ' privilege 1'
        return self.configure(cmd)
```
